That was really kind of a step back towards where I am now. And in that role, I was focused on their port application. Really out talking to portfolio managers about how do you manage your portfolios. The job is teaching someone how to use a Bloomberg function. From my perspective, you can't really do that well if you don't understand their process. So I learned a lot about how different managers think about their process. And you figure out in an industry where we all think we're right and we'll sit around and tell everyone why we're right. And we'll try to convince everyone you're right. You realize that there's a lot of different ways to do what we do. And people think about things. And a different ways. None of us know what the future is. So it's really how do we create our call it probabilistic view of the future and how do different people do that. So really interesting. And that's a free site for anybody who wants to go to our website and access those. Also being involved in our asset allocation. So we're a big part of that. And eventually, as you mentioned, I'm the head of that group running a number of different multi asset strategies that we manage or sub advise for as many of your listeners know, research affiliates were really around publishing research and sub advising for others. We don't actually manage any dollars specifically as Rob Arnott likes to say it. We're an investment manager that doesn't manage any assets.
